-- Ugandan Coffee Development Authority’s Robusta Prices
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-03-22T08:50:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-22/ugandan-coffee-development-authority-s-robusta-prices-table-.html
The  Uganda  Coffee Development
Authority today quoted indicative prices for exports of robusta,
which accounts for 85 percent of the country’s bean shipments.  Uganda is  Africa ’s second-biggest coffee producer, after
 Ethiopia , and the continent’s largest robusta coffee producer.  Nearby refers to deliveries to be made within 45 days and
indicative prices are used by exporters to determine prices.  Prices are in U.S. cents a pound, based on free-on-board
rail/truck from Kampala, the capital:  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
